  "input": {
    "question_id": "PG-1",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are audit and assurance policies established, documented, and approved?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY's Audit Committee has established pre-approval policies and procedures applicable to all services provided by our independent registered public accountants, in accordance with SEC rules. The pre-approval policy takes two approaches: services may be pre-approved pursuant to policies and procedures established by the Audit Committee that are detailed as to a particular class of service (\"class pre-approval\"), or, where a class of service has not received class pre-approval, the service requires specific pre-approval by the Audit Committee before it is provided (\"specific pre-approval\"). A list of services that have received class pre-approval from the Audit Committee (or its delegate) is attached to our Audit and Permitted Non-Audit Services Pre-Approval Policy, a copy of which is publicly available on our website. Adherence to the policy is demonstrated in practice: for 2023, 100% of the fees associated with the independent registered public accounting firm services were pre-approved by the Audit Committee. On behalf of the Board, the Audit Committee also oversees the operation of a comprehensive system of internal controls with respect to the integrity of our financial statements and reports, compliance with laws, regulations and corporate policies, and the qualifications, performance and independence of our independent registered public accounting firm.",
